Evercore Hires BofA’s Magro for Industrial-Consumer Banking

-- B y   L a u r a   M a r c i n e k
-- 
2011-06-01T12:59:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/evercore-hires-bofa-s-magro-for-industrial-consumer-banking.html
Evercore Partners Inc. (EVR) , the
investment bank founded by former U.S. Deputy Treasury Secretary
 Roger Altman , hired Anthony J. Magro as a senior managing
director focusing on industrial and consumer businesses.  Magro, 57, was most recently a vice chairman of global
investment banking at Bank of America Merrill Lynch, New York-
based Evercore said today in a statement. He was previously
global head of the industrial and natural resources groups and
mergers and acquisitions at Charlotte, North Carolina-based Bank
of America. Magro was also global head of mergers and
acquisitions at Bear Stearns Cos. before joining Bank of America
10 years ago, according to the statement.  Evercore has been adding managing directors from some of
the biggest investment banks, including Raymond Strong III from
 Goldman Sachs Group Inc. (GS)  for its energy group and Eric Mandl
from  UBS AG (UBSN)  in its technology and Internet banking group. Magro
has advised Tyco International Ltd, Kellogg Co. and Energizer
Holdings Inc. on transactions, according to the statement.  “Tony has a long history of advising his clients on
matters of significant complexity and strategic importance,”
Altman said today in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Marcinek in New York at 
 lmarcinek3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Scheer at 
 dscheer@bloomberg.net . 